Subject: Re: [T2] Compufire Question w/ SVDA

Trey Jung wrote:
> When they go bad is it an all or nothing thing ? I'm thinking if the Compufire
> is going bad, it goes bad and the bus wouldn't start at all. Correct? or can
> they slowly die?

Most of the points replacement parts that I have heard of failing have 
been a sudden loss of it's ability to open and close the circuit. I do 
know that Mark Dearing had an issue with one similar unit that started 
to act strange before dying, but that is the only time I have personally 
heard of it's slowly going out.

> It starts, just dies when coming up to a Stop Sign or Red Light.
> 
> Trying to get to the Root Cause........

With that in mind, I would first check for a vacuum leak. Those leaks 
tend to start messing with the idle first.

